body:
IMO it is OK for `DoFnRunners` to sprawl as a collection of ways to get a `DoFnRunner`.

The name `DoFnRunner` is actually misleading. This interface does not have to have anything to do with a `DoFn`:

```java
public interface DoFnRunner<InputT, OutputT> {
  void startBundle();
  void processElement(WindowedValue<InputT> elem);
  void finishBundle();
}
```

If you called this `BundleProcessor` then you would probably be fine to have all of these:

 - `BundleProcessors.forDoFn(...)`
 - `BundleProcessors.forOldDoFn(...)`
 - `BundleProcessors.forDoFnInvoker(...)`

To do the last one, you need to be able to get the `DoFnSignature` from a `DoFnInvoker`. You probably don't actually need the `DoFn`.
